shared_text:
Lakeside Jr./Sr. High School
Yesterday at 6:03 AM ·

Today is the 19th anniversary of the terror attacks of September 11, 2001. There’s not a Lakeside student walking our halls that was alive on that day. Some of our teachers are even too young to remember the tragedy and the aftermath. The only positive thing to come from all the death and despair was a sense of unity and the rallying of one American people. Politics and division was put aside for a time and we focused on the things that unite us rather than divide us. Our shared humanity. Politicians no longer demonized one another and demagogues did not profit off of the fear and hate that so many of our citizens have for each other. We were not white Americans and black Americans. We were not Red States and Blue States. We were Americans. We were the United States. So even though many have forgotten, Lakeside remembers and has made this video for the anniversary.

J. L. Jones Elementary
September 8 at 4:17 PM ·

The 2020 Census counts the population in all 50 states, the District of Columbia, and five U.S. territories. A complete and accurate count is critical for all Louisiana communities, because the results of the 2020 Census will affect community funding, congressional representation, and more.

The 2020 Census count impacts the federal funds that communities receive each year for programs and services that are critical for schools, students, and younger children, such as:
-Special education, Head Start, after-school programs, and classroom technology.
-Food assistance, including free and reduced-price school lunches.
-Maternal and child health programs.
-Planning, preparedness, and recovery efforts for all types of national emergencies, including COVID-19.

Self-responses, which can be completed online at https://my2020census.gov/, by phone, or by mail until September 30, ensures federal funding to support Louisiana students.

E.S. Richardson Elementary
August 31 at 8:15 PM ·

Please help us welcome Miss Wolf! She will be teaching 5th grade science and social studies for our Tech Connect Virtual Program. Miss Wolf was asked to tell us a little about herself. She said “my family is from West Monroe, LA. I am the youngest of three kids. However, I am a twin so I am only one minute younger than my middle sister. I graduated from the University of Louisiana at Monroe in December 2011 and moved to New Iberia, LA. I have taught a variety of elementary and middle school classes throughout my eight years in South Louisiana. I love walking my dog, taking naps, and eating tacos. This is my first year at Richardson and I am EXTREMELY excited about getting to know every one of my students.” We are SO GLAD you are at ESR! 🍭🍡🍦🧁🍩🍬

Insurance will be offered only on the day that Chromebooks are deployed. This insurance will cover damaged Chromebooks. The cost is $25.00 for the insurance. However, this insurance does not cover if the Chromebook is lost or stolen.
If your child is attending through the Brick & Mortar option, letters will be mailed to your homes this week indicating what group your children are in. Our intent for A or B Hybrid grouping was for all students in the same household to attend school on the same days. If you feel there was an error in your child’s grouping and siblings were not grouped together, please call the school immediately.

Please welcome Tamaya Shine to Webster Junior High School. Her autobiography is attached! My name is Tayama Shine. I am a wife, the mother of four young men, as well as a proud Grandmother. I enjoy reading, family time and helping others.

I have been in education for 25 years; 12 years with Webster Parish Head Start and my latter years with Webster Parish School Board as a Second/Third Grade teacher at J. L. Jones Elementary. I am proud to join the Webster Wolves Family as a 6th ELA teacher.

My classroom mission states that :
My students will always SHINE
S- trive for success
H- ave fun learning
I- nspire each other
N- ever give up
E- xcel in all they do
Because I believe that all children can learn and achieve success!

August 13 at 9:38 AM ·

Please welcome Ms. Randle to Webster Junior High School. She will be teaching 6th grade Math. Her biography and photo are attached!

Ms. Randle is a native of Bradley, AR and a graduate of the University of Central Arkansas. She holds a Bachelor of Science in Psychology and Business Administration. Ms. Randle is transitioning as a Captain in the active duty Army and is proud to continue service in the U.S. Army Reserve. No stranger to the classroom, Ms. Randle previously taught 6th Grade Math in Texas. A self-proclaimed Marvel fanatic and food connoisseur, she enjoys organizing items, traveling, reading, and empowering young minds. Ms. Randle is blessed to have the support of her fiance, T'Ryan, and bonus son Ivion. She is pursuing her Masters of Public Administration and is excited to join the Webster Junior High team!

shared_text:
Webster Junior High School
August 12 at 9:00 AM ·

Due to multiple concerns, Webster Junior High is offering an “in person” registration opportunity for you to register your child if you were unable to register him/her through our online registration form. This registration needs to be completed for every student regardless if he/she attended one of our schools during the 2019-20 school year. Webster Junior High will be offering registration assistance on Monday, August 17, 2020. Please bring with you two proofs of residence. Registration time slots are assigned by the last name, to assist with social distancing guidelines.

A-E 8:00-9:30
F-K 9:30-11:00
L-S 11:00-12:30
T-Z 12:30-2:00

Parents must wear a mask.

We are happy to be able to offer all of our students a chromebook for their academic pursuits this year; however, this technology cannot be issued to your child if he/she is not officially registered as a WPSB student.

If you have been calling for preregistration to get tested on Saturday July 11 in Minden at Webster Jr. High School and have been told something different about the testing, just show up and fill out the paperwork on site.

It takes about 1 minute per person to fill out paperwork.

Testing is for all school age children and older. There is no co-pay or out of pocket expense for you.

Testing is done by qualified legal licensed medical personnel. All you need is a valid ID and your insurance information if you have any.

post_text:
Parents and guardians: If your child was enrolled in our Webster Parish schools this year, please apply.....Each child is eligible for $285 worth of P-EBT benefits, but you must apply. It might take you a bit to get through, but we have had MANY parents who have been able to get through and the application is very quick and easy. You will need your child's social security number during the application. Please share with other families of WPSB students. We are a 100% free breakfast/lunch district, so all of our students are eligible.

Have a great day! :)

post_text:
Parents,

We would like to first thank you for your patience and understanding as we navigate through these unchartered waters known as COVID-19. In an effort to bring closure to the current academic school year, we are working on finalizing grades. In order to complete this process, our Parent Command Center will be unavailable until the end of May. Report cards will be mailed June 1st. Thank you for your support and for remaining safe.
text:
Parents,

We would like to first thank you for your patience and understanding as we navigate through these unchartered waters known as COVID-19. In an effort to bring closure to the current academic school year, we are working on finalizing grades. In order to complete this process, our Parent Command Center will be unavailable until the end of May. Report cards will be mailed June 1st. Thank you for your support and for remaining safe.

YEARBOOK SALE!!!

NWUE 2019-2020 YEARBOOK WILL BE SOLD AT THE SCHOOL ‪ON MONDAY, MAY 18TH FROM 9:00 TO 12:00‬. YEARBOOKS WILL BE SOLD ON A FIRST COME, FIRST SERVE BASIS. THE COST IS $25.00, CASH ONLY PLEASE.

DUE TO COVID 19 THE FOLLOWING INSTRUCTIONS MUST BE STRICTLY FOLLOWED:
· MONEY SHOULD BE PLACED IN AN ENVELOPE WITH THE CHILD’S NAME ON IT.
· DRIVE UP TO THE MAIN ENTRANCE TO THE SCHOOL
· PLACE YOUR MONEY ENVELOPE ON ONE OF THE CARTS ON THE SIDEWALK AND RETURN TO YOUR VEHICLE.
· THE MONEY WILL BE RETRIEVED AND A RECEIPT WILL BE WRITTEN AND PLACED IN THE YEARBOOK WHICH WILL THEN BE PLACED ON THE CART.

THANK YOU FOR YOUR SUPPORT OF NWUE!!

Please contact Ms. Brantley with any concerns.

Email: Beatha.brantley@websterpsb.org or you can send her a message on DoJo.

Teacher Appreciation Week ~
May 4th-8th
Show teachers & staff how much you appreciate them at Browning!

Make Me Smile Monday: send a selfie to your teacher and tell them how much you miss them.

Amazing Friday: Show your teacher how “AMAZing’ they are with a gift card. (not to exceed $25)

You may mail cards, notes, or gift cards to your special teacher at:
Browning Elementary School
Attention: Teacher's Name
505 Herrington Drive,
Springhill, LA 71075
